Looking at the C code:
```c
case CONTROLLER_INPUT_TEMPERATURE:
    controller->has_valid_temperature = true;
    controller->previous_temperature_c = controller->last_temperature_c;
    controller->last_temperature_c = input.temperature_c;
    controller->last_temperature_ms = input.now_ms;

    /* Update state based on current level and new temperature */
    if (controller->has_valid_level) {
        controller_update_state(controller, controller->last_level, input.temperature_c, input.now_ms);
    }
```

So the C code updates `previous_temperature_c` BEFORE calling `controller_update_state`. But my mock doesn't do that. Let me fix this:

